snippet: The Obama administration is embarking on a crucial effort to re-enroll the seven million who are covered and to attract more uninsured Americans, as a three-month enrollment period begins.
abstract: Affordable Care Act will face substantial new test when second enrollment period for buying health insurance begins and proponents embark on three-month mission to persuade millions more Americans to sign up; officials are promising smoother enrollment experience than last time, but current enrollment period brings with it complications.

byline.original: By ABBY GOODNOUGH and ROBERT PEAR

lead_paragraph: The Obama administration is embarking on a crucial effort to re-enroll the seven million who are covered and to attract more uninsured Americans, as a three-month enrollment period begins.

headline.main: Health Care’s Next Test: Getting More to Enroll
